&lt;p&gt;At the Senior level, this role is expected to operate with broad autonomy and influence, proactively identifying systemic risks, anticipating environment-specific failure modes, and shaping system design decisions early in the product lifecycle. You will partner closely with software engineering, quality, DevOps, and product teams to ensure the product behaves safely, predictably, and reliably across development, validation, and real-world enterprise deployments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and evolve the system-level architecture of a Windows-based IVD software product deployed to customer environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a system-level technical authority, influencing architecture and design decisions without formal people management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, configure, and support product deployments using IIS, SQL Server, WSL, and Docker across on-premises, virtualized, and cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate, identify, and mitigate environment-specific risks across Windows and Linux systems, virtual machines, containers, networking, and cloud infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and stabilize a distributed product maintained over multiple years across a large enterprise install base (100+ customer installations).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead deep root-cause analysis of complex issues spanning application behavior, operating systems, databases, containers, and infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, document, and enforce supported deployment models, environment assumptions, constraints, and known failure modes.&lt;/li&gt;
